reviewText: I bought this for a gift for a sick friend. He loves it!

First of all, it's really hard to see Randy Quaid try to play such a serious character.  It seems like a different actor might have been more convinving.  I would have guessed that this movie was filmed in the 80s because of the quality.  The sound and the quality weren't very good....maybe because it's a VHS version.  It is a hard movie to find though so a VHS is what I settled for.
Movie was just as described, I enjoyed it, it kept me guessing until the end. Just when I thought I had figured it out, I was proved wrong. Thanks for the great movie.
